# Reflection

## What I Learned

Fact checking involves more than deciding whether something is true or false. Some claims require additional context, while others cannot currently be verified because they concern future events or subjective predictions.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

When evaluating real-world claims, I would verify information using multiple high-quality sources rather than relying on a single reference. I would also distinguish between factual statements, opinions, predictions, and misleading claims more explicitly.

